# Documentation Style Guide

## Brand Guidelines

**IMPORTANT**: The product name "biorouter" should ALWAYS be written in lowercase in all documentation, blog posts, and any content within this documentation directory. When referring to the project name, use "BioRouter" with capital B and R.

- ✅ Correct: "biorouter", "using biorouter", "biorouter provides", "BioRouter project"
- ❌ Incorrect: "BioRouter" (when referring to the product), "Biorouter"

This is a brand guideline that must be strictly followed.

## Context

This rule applies to:
- All markdown files in `/docs/`
- All blog posts in `/blog/`
- README files
- Configuration files with user-facing text
- Any other documentation content

When editing or creating content in this documentation directory, always ensure "biorouter" uses lowercase letters when referring to the product, and "BioRouter" when referring to the project name.
